reviews.text: they have recently implied a new queue ticket system and this is absolutely a disater. A large group (9ppl) of us had been coming here for lunch several times before and we knew that we have to wait for a bit more but thats fine with us, but this is all before they have this new queue system. Now NO WAITING STAFF would assist you anymore and they will NEVER NEVER NEVER ever arrange a table for you even if you got your ticket earlier than most of other tickets, we have picked our ticket here at 12.10 ish and we supposed to be the 2nd table for a group more than 6, waited for 45 or 50 mins, Only like one or two groups that were more than 5 could get their table, our group had to rage about that to get staff moving other customers to tables around in order to get us a place while there were like more than 40 small tables have been served. IF YOU ARE NOT PREPARED OR WANTED TO SERVE A BIG GROUP THAN STOP ALLOWING PEOPLE TO GET TICKET AND LET YOUR CUSTOMERS WAIT UNTIL THE END OF WORLD. They have never intended to serve a large table anyway, since their table layout is easy to move around so its not an excuse for them just that they prefer to let small group get in and out rather than reserve tables for large group. If we did not complained to any of the staff, we may never get our table. Food is good but I will never recommend anyone to eat in anymore. Get your system right and train your staff on how to work along with that please. There's definitely a management problem. Even you put a queue ticket machine here does not mean you dont need to monitor.

Serving up authentic Taiwanese style beef noodles and regional Taiwanese cuisine. The noodles are springy and the broth is flavourful. Located just above it’s other Taiwanese competitor, Teawood. 

This place boast a huge lunch crowd as it’s lunch deals are amazingly priced. The pork cutlet with braised meat rice is only $69
Food decent quality but teawood downstairs is better. But poor service and irritating music
Haven't tried other dishes but you will not be disappointed with the beef noodle. They do it right.
Just one word „DELICIOUS“ 😋

Was here for dinner with friend, and the food is not as good as mentioned. Also the seating is a bit unpleasant and dirty.

Nice place with songs from Taiwan playing as background music. Delicious food and good place for dinner as a group. You can have the Taiwan food and drinks here. quite special that you need to paid first before eating. But you can leave whenever you are finished. Give a try.
Compared to local restaurants, the food quality is ok and price reasonable. Environment and service is above average.
A good place for Taiwanese beef noodle.The service is good and fast. Budget is around $80/head for dinner.
